Intro One of the biggest benefits of Docker images is their immutability. Once they&rsquo;re built, they don&rsquo;t change. Built once, would work forever&hellip; That&rsquo;s how nightmares of security guys starts &#x1f923;
We have then two contradictory concepts:
flowchart LR id1(Keep it stable) <---> id2(Keep is up to date and secure) For day to day work, usually first concept wins. You want your builds stable and try to avoid tempting distractions of upgrading log4j to latest version&hellip; Who knows what might break.

TL;DR While reasoning is important, readers may not be interested in all the frustrations I experienced while figuring out how to get things done. If you&rsquo;re looking for a quick solution, skip to the &ldquo;What eventually worked?&rdquo; section. However, if you&rsquo;re interested in the thought process behind the solution, keep reading.
Why? Some might bother why the hell I&rsquo;d like to make my life so hard? &#x1f923;
